mlx function put_image vs destroy_image

I place images on the window using the following line - 
	mlx_put_image_to_window(game->mlx_ptr, game->win_ptr, \
				pic, col, row);
I then free the images using the following line - 
	mlx_destroy_image(game->mlx_ptr, game->image.wall);

Although I have destroyed the images, the window still displays the images why?

The window will still display the images even after you destroy them because 
the window maintains a reference to the image data until the window itself 
is destroyed or the image is replaced.
